30/01/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- NATO Assistant Secretary General for Defence and Planning Operations Edgar Buckley ended his visit to Bucharest on Wednesday (29 January) with a positive assessment of ongoing army reforms.
Buckley said the country had formed an enthusiastic team to complete the process.
Key components include troop reductions and defence capability upgrades.
Defence Minister Ioan Mircea Pascu said later that the delegation had not discussed Romania's participation in a possible campaign against Iraq.
(Rompres - 30/01/03)
